// Police Act 1967 [Act 344] — the STOP powers a citizen actually meets on the
// road, chunked as the front door of the "can they search my phone?" cluster
// (the CPC file carries the search/arrest/computerized-data spine): s24
// (stop+detain a person to demand a licence/permit; stop+SEARCH WITHOUT
// WARRANT a vehicle or vessel on reasonable suspicion — note the limit: the
// vehicle power is vehicles/vessels, NOT a general power to rummage a person
// or their phone; plus the 48-hour vehicle-detention rule) and s26 (road
// barriers — the roadblock power, the offence of not stopping, and the
// no-warrant arrest hook). REJECTED: s25 (aircraft — not a citizen roadside
// encounter), s27-27C (assemblies — deleted by Act A1421 anyway), s20 (duties
// generally — no distinct power a stop turns on).
